mods.abstract: The California Magazine of Western Square and Round Dancing by the Square Dancers of Southern California. This edition includes a table of contents which lists the following: "From the Floor", "Square Dance Date Book", "On the Record and Record Report", "As I See It", "The Dancer's Walkthru", "Square Dance Floats on Parade", ""What Ever Happened to Kirby Todd?"", "N.Y. World's Fair Puts Square Dancing on the Map", "Ladies on the Square: "Engineered" Sleeves for Square Dancing Dresses", "Style Series: The "Little Things" That Count", "Overseas Dateline", "Round the Outside Ring", "Sets in Order Workshop", "Caller of the Month: Billy Lewis", "Paging the Roundancers: Dan and Mildred Hulin; Bud and Betty Sibbald", and "Experimental Lab: Bend Thru".
